IRS990.Description: PERFORMS PEER REVIEWS ON MEMBER ASSOCIATIONS ANNUALLY TO DETERMINE COMPLIANCE WITH YWCA STANDARDS. PROVIDES TECHNICAL ASSISTANCE ANNUALLY IN THE AREAS OF PROGRAM DEVELOPMENT, BUDGET PREPARATION AND OTHER PROGRAM AREAS. PROVIDES TRAINING TO MEMBER ASSOCIATIONS THROUGHOUT THE YEAR. THERE ARE 41 MEMBER ASSOCIATIONS.

GeneralExplanation.Identifier: EXPLANATION ON VOLUNTEERS AND TYPES OF SERVICES OR BENEFITS
GeneralExplanation.Explanation: VOLUNTEERS PROVIDE GOVERNANCE AND ASSISTANCE WITH CARRYING OUT THE REGIONAL COUNCIL'S PROGRAMS.
THE ORGANIZATION'S BOARD OF DIRECTORS IS MADE UP OF THE PRESIDENTS AND EXECUTIVE DIRECTORS OF THE MEMBER YWCA'S, AS WELL AS SEVERAL EMPLOYEES IN DIRECTOR POSITIONS.

GeneralExplanation.Identifier: ORGANIZATION'S PROCESS USED TO REVIEW FORM 990
GeneralExplanation.Explanation: THE CPA PREPARING FORM 990 SENDS A DRAFT COPY TO THE CO-CHAIR WHO IN TURN MAKES IT AVAILABLE TO THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS.
THE ORGANIZATION MONITORS AND ENFORCES COMPLIANCE WITH ITS WRITTEN CONFLICT OF INTEREST POLICY BY MEANS OF A QUESTIONNAIRE.

A COMPARISON STUDY OF SALARIES IN SIMILAR POSITIONS IS MADE WITH OTHER LOCAL AND REGIONAL ASSOCIATIONS AND A RECOMMENDATION IS PUT FORWARD TO THE FINANCE COMMITTEE. THE FINANCE COMMITTEE IN TURN MAKES A RECOMMENDATION TO THE BOARD, WHICH APPROVES THE SALARY.
